column9:
This is Face with Tears of Joy, A yellow face with a big grin, uplifted eyebrows, and smiling eyes, each shedding a tear from laughing so hard. Widely used to show something is funny or pleasing. It has been used by 3838853523 times by 2022.

Named the Oxford Dictionaries 2015 Word of the Year, and the most used emoji on all platforms from 2011-2021. Briefly overtaken as the top emoji on Twitter in 2021 by 😭 Loudly Crying Face, though as of January 2022 it has reclaimed its top position on the platform.

😂 being overtaken by 😭 can be attributed to several factors:

The "Face with Tears of Joy" emoji (😂) has been the most popular emoji for over a decade, leading to overexposure.
The "Loudly Crying Face" emoji (😭) is more versatile. Depending on the context, it can represent laughter or sadness. Its dual purpose has helped it secure the top spot.
The COVID-19 pandemic may have reduced the number of moments we wanted to use 😂 and increased the instances where we reached for 😭.
Whether you are celebrating getting vaccinated ("😭💉"), laughing out loud in a group chat ("😭💬"), crying in embarrassment ("😭🙇"), or longing for a return to normal life ("😭💃"), the 😭 Loudly Crying Face has likely been with you when 😂 was not.

This does not mean we have stopped laughing. Instead, we now use 😭 to express every kind of emotion, such as laughter, sadness, pride, joy, relief.
😭😭😭 makes you laugh. 😭😭😭 makes you cry.

This emoji is called Loudly Crying Face, a yellow face with an open mouth wailing and streams of heavy tears flowing from closed eyes. May convey inconsolable grief but also other intense feelings, such as uncontrollable laughter, pride or overwhelming joy.

In March 2021, 😭 Loudly Crying Face became the most popular emoji on Twitter, which has been used by 1749533868 times by 2022. It held this position until January 2022, when 😂 Face with Tears of Joy returned as the top emoji on the platform.

From the table, we can see that the usage of 😭 (Loudly Crying Face) increased sharply from 2018 to 2019, likely influenced by the pandemic. It reached its peak in February 2022 and then began to decline.

Pleading Face, one yellow face with furrowed eyebrows, a small frown, and large, "puppy dog" eyes, as if begging, pleading, or yearning (possibly even in a NSFW manner, depending on the context). May also represent adoration or feeling touched by a loving gesture. Huawei's design for this emoji includes a pair of 🙏 Folded Hands.

At its peak the Pleading Face was the third most popular emoji used on Twitter,used by 1515151515 times in Twitter, and was the most commonly found emoji in tweets that include hearts. Used in sequence with pointing hands to indicate a bashful or shy pose (🥺👉👈) particularly on TikTok.This emoji shares many similarities with 😭 (Loudly Crying Face).

Both are highly versatile and cover a wide range of emotions. Neither has a fixed meaning, making them suitable for various contexts.

Recent use of 😭 (Loudly Crying Face) indicates its tears are incredibly versatile. Depending on the context, this emoji can express joy or sadness, pride or embarrassment, love or grief. No wonder 😭 is so popular.
